    "body": "This is expected behaviour. When you upload a single file, that file is then available at the root of the resulting hash:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ echo \"data\" > file.txt\r\n\r\n$ swarm up file.txt\r\ne23b5dc2df754b15890235a4101976f5798a2e9b952a6310f1f66e8df73aba36\r\n\r\n$ curl http://localhost:8500/bzz:/e23b5dc2df754b15890235a4101976f5798a2e9b952a6310f1f66e8df73aba36\r\ndata\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf you want the file to be available at a specific path, you currently need to do a recursive upload of a directory containing that file:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ tmpdir=\"$(mktemp --directory)\"\r\n\r\n$ echo \"data\" > \"${tmpdir}/file.txt\"\r\n\r\n$ swarm --recursive up \"${tmpdir}\"\r\ne85a0ced0f3e4cda0d59e4909a0d03e27516e62908668b4220cd3a27bce01b25\r\n\r\n$ curl http://localhost:8500/bzz:/e85a0ced0f3e4cda0d59e4909a0d03e27516e62908668b4220cd3a27bce01b25/file.txt\r\ndata\r\n```",
